In-House patients:
 Faeces Routine Culture is not routinely performed on hospital in-patients. Clinician to contact Microbiology lab if testing is required on ward samples.
 Clostridium difficile toxin.
 Norovirus.
 Viral Studies.
 Ova and parasites-see section 10.9.14 below.
 CPE/CRE, ESBL/VRE
Rota/Adenovirus

Salmonella, Shigella, Vibrio parahemolyticus

Faeces Routine Testing by Bio Fire® PCR: on ED, OPD and samples approved by the Consultant Microbiologist. BioFire® PCR tests for the following targets;

Bacteria: Campylobacter, Clostridium difficile toxin A/B, Plesiomonas shigelloides, Salmonella, Vibrio, Yersinia enterocolitica.

Diarrhoeagenic E.coli/Shigella: Enteroaggregative E.coli (EAEC), Enteropathogenic E.coli (EPEC), Enterotoxigenic E.coli (ETEC), Shiga-like toxin-producing E.coli (STEC(VTEC)) stx1/stx2, E.coli 0157, Shigella, Enteroinvasive E.coli (EIEC)

Parasites: Cryptosporidium, Cyclospora cayetanensis, Entamoeba histolytic, Giardia lamblia

Viruses: Adenovirus F40/41, Astrovirus, Norovirus GI/GII, Rotavirus A, Sapovirus.

----------------------------------------------------
For Salmonella + shigs the lack of color change in the sugar bottles indicate the possibility of infection
salmo + shig != color change

commensals produce a urea sucrose sugars color change. 
